      <bioghist id="aspace_7aa092ee0e10742b95256dab64f6c186">
         <head>George H. Bissell, 1821-1884</head>
         <p>George H. Bissell was co-founder of the Pennsylvania Rock Oil Company, the first petroleum company in the United States, and of the Adirondack Pulp Mills, among many other business ventures.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ab7517b3d9488b7e03dea8a3b32c352c">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of printed material, business records, and photographs that document the Bissell family and the foundations of the American petroleum industry in the 1850s. The collection is bound in seven volumes: two volumes of printed material relating to petroleum and other industries, three volumes of records of the Pennsylvania Rock Oil Company and the Adirondack Pulp Mills that document the creation and early growth of the companies, and two Bissell family photograph albums.</p>
         <p>Printed material in this collection is described in Orbis (Yale's online catalog) and the catalog records can be reviewed by searching for GEN MSS 788 in Call Number (Local).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
